column80:
-Sana ay pigilan ang patuloy na paglabas ng mga virus sa oras na matapos ang naturang mini game.
-Sana ay naka-focus agad ang typing cursor sa text field ng CAPTCHA game.
-Sana ay hindi magrehistro bilang click sa mismong pop-up ang pagclick lamang sa title bar.
-Maaaring makadagdag sa thrill kung magkakaroon ng timer, pabilis nang pabilis ang bawat mini game sa bawat iterasyon, at gawing layunin para sa manlalaro ang makasagot ng maraming minigame sa loob ng oras na itatakda ng timer. (Tulad sa larong Dumb Ways to Die)

column80:
On the survey: When I receive an OTP without knowing what triggered it, I should be prompted to secure the accounts by checking logs or changing the passwords since some OTPs are sent after one tries to login with the correct credentials on an unknown device. 

For the game: The game is OK! but it feels very much more of a quiz than a game, maybe making it more puzzle like might be better, also making the puzzles much more difficult might be better such as instead of using "faceb00k.com" as an example, making the user first fail to distinguish "fɑcebook.com" (or any other obscure typography that isn't really noticeable) as an illegitimate site might give the game and information more "shock value" to stick.

column80: May nakita lang akong typo sa identifying phishing emails - yung "tumtugma" ang nakalagay imbes na "tumutugma". Additionally, doon sa part ng game na iyon, I think pwede niyong ilagay na multiple parts of email ang nagiindicate na phishing scam siya. Doon sa na-experience ko kasi, parang yung sagot ay naghihingi ng details, pero nagpapahiwatig din siya na scam from the email address nung sender kasi di siya official FB email. Then yung protektahan yung computer mula sa virus, di ko agad narealize na kailangan pindutin yung virus para ma-deads sila, so sana may instruction for that. Other than that, well done!!!
